s and hates regression, we forget that there is much significance to looking backward. We seek to invent solutions, but real antidotes are not invented &#8212; they&#8217;re found, right beside the cause of the very problem they remedy.</p><p>We can regard ourselves objectively (without narcissism) and honor the desires and histories that make us who we are. When our relationship is frayed, we need to examine the backside of why it&#8217;s falling apart. When our mental state is fragile, we should look closely at what&#8217;s behind all of our troubles. Just like how the ugly backstreets make up the crotch of a beautiful city &#8212; taboo, dirty (even if just figuratively), yet somehow vital in the conception of urban legends that give the city its soul &#8212; we too conceal a shadow that we wrestle with.</p><p>Anasyrma (along with <a href="https://www.theplurisociety.com/p/on-eroticism-sensuality-and-romance">eroticism</a>) is an odd fascination that usually belongs in the profane, but it is also involved in the sacred:</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theplurisociety.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.theplurisociety.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theplurisociety.com/p/when-life-lifts-up-her-skirt?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.theplurisociety.com/p/when-life-lifts-up-her-skirt?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p>
